        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the difference between AI marketing tools and AI-native marketing?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "AI marketing tools are individual products that automate specific tasks (copy generation, scheduling, reporting). AI-native marketing is a workflow design philosophy: instead of adding AI tools to existing processes, you redesign the entire marketing operation around what AI can do reliably. A business using AI tools might generate faster first drafts. A business with AI-native marketing has eliminated 60–70% of manual production work and redirected that time to strategy and customer relationships.",
          },
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is vision-intelligence?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "vision-intelligence is an AI marketing platform built specifically for DACH SMEs. It provides three layers: a content production system with German-language brand voice templates, a purchase-intent content layer that identifies and answers buyer decision-stage questions in German, and an intelligence layer that delivers weekly automated performance summaries. It is designed for companies with one generalist or a small team where the founder's time is the primary constraint. Currently in beta with 3 DACH SME pilots ahead of a July 2026 public release.",
          },
